{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":59,"text":"One in four people suffer from some sort of mental illness,"},{"time":3983,"text":"so if it was one, two, three, four, it's you, sir."},{"time":8277,"text":"You. Yeah. (Laughter)"},{"time":9836,"text":"With the weird teeth. And you next to him. (Laughter)"},{"time":13184,"text":"You know who you are."},{"time":14239,"text":"Actually, that whole row isn't right. (Laughter)"},{"time":16636,"text":"That's not good. Hi. Yeah. Real bad. Don't even look at me. (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":21810,"text":"I am one of the one in four. Thank you."},{"time":26923,"text":"I think I inherit it from my mother, who,"},{"time":29933,"text":"used to crawl around the house on all fours."},{"time":32747,"text":"She had two sponges in her hand, and then she had two"},{"time":35794,"text":"tied to her knees. My mother was completely absorbent. (Laughter)"},{"time":40376,"text":"And she would crawl around behind me going,"},{"time":42684,"text":"\"Who brings footprints into a building?!\""},{"time":46249,"text":"So that was kind of a clue that things weren't right."},{"time":48599,"text":"So before I start, I would like to thank"},{"time":53791,"text":"the makers of Lamotrigine, Sertraline, and Reboxetine,"},{"time":58477,"text":"because without those few simple chemicals, I would not be vertical today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":63400,"text":"So how did it start?"},{"time":68237,"text":"My mental illness -- well, I'm not even going to talk about my mental illness."},{"time":72356,"text":"What am I going to talk about? Okay."},{"time":74669,"text":"I always dreamt that, when I had my final breakdown,"},{"time":79071,"text":"it would be because I had a deep Kafkaesque"},{"time":81610,"text":"existentialist revelation,"},{"time":84023,"text":"or that maybe Cate Blanchett would play me and she would win an Oscar for it. (Laughter)"},{"time":88368,"text":"But that's not what happened. I had my breakdown"},{"time":91475,"text":"during my daughter's sports day."},{"time":93465,"text":"There were all the parents sitting in a parking lot"},{"time":97190,"text":"eating food out of the back of their car -- only the English --"},{"time":101197,"text":"eating their sausages. They loved their sausages. (Laughter)"},{"time":107424,"text":"Lord and Lady Rigor Mortis were nibbling on the tarmac,"},{"time":112056,"text":"and then the gun went off and all the girlies started running,"},{"time":114519,"text":"and all the mummies went, \"Run! Run Chlamydia! Run!\" (Laughter)"},{"time":119730,"text":"\"Run like the wind, Veruca! Run!\""},{"time":123598,"text":"And all the girlies, girlies running, running, running,"},{"time":126065,"text":"everybody except for my daughter, who was just standing"},{"time":129010,"text":"at the starting line, just waving,"},{"time":131777,"text":"because she didn't know she was supposed to run."},{"time":134108,"text":"So I took to my bed for about a month, and when I woke up"},{"time":138457,"text":"I found I was institutionalized, and when I saw the other inmates,"},{"time":143050,"text":"I realized that I had found my people, my tribe. (Laughter)"},{"time":147442,"text":"Because they became my only friends, they became my friends,"},{"time":150930,"text":"because very few people that I knew -- Well, I wasn't"},{"time":153928,"text":"sent a lot of cards or flowers. I mean, if I had had a broken leg"},{"time":157298,"text":"or I was with child I would have been inundated,"},{"time":159462,"text":"but all I got was a couple phone calls telling me to perk up."},{"time":163138,"text":"Perk up."},{"time":164838,"text":"Because I didn't think of that. (Laughter)"},{"time":169545,"text":"(Laughter) (Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":172845,"text":"Because, you know, the one thing, one thing that you get with this disease,"},{"time":177122,"text":"this one comes with a package, is you get a real sense of shame,"},{"time":181088,"text":"because your friends go, \"Oh come on, show me the lump,"},{"time":183400,"text":"show me the x-rays,\" and of course you've got nothing to show,"},{"time":185811,"text":"so you're, like, really disgusted with yourself because you're thinking,"},{"time":188905,"text":"\"I'm not being carpet-bombed. I don't live in a township.\""},{"time":191721,"text":"So you start to hear these abusive voices, but you don't hear one abusive voice,"},{"time":195169,"text":"you hear about a thousand -- 100,000 abusive voices,"},{"time":198028,"text":"like if the Devil had Tourette's, that's what it would sound like."},{"time":202037,"text":"But we all know in here, you know, there is no Devil,"},{"time":204665,"text":"there are no voices in your head."},{"time":206544,"text":"You know that when you have those abusive voices,"},{"time":208218,"text":"all those little neurons get together and in that little gap"},{"time":211119,"text":"you get a real toxic \"I want to kill myself\" kind of chemical,"},{"time":214777,"text":"and if you have that over and over again on a loop tape,"},{"time":217523,"text":"you might have yourself depression."},{"time":219419,"text":"Oh, and that's not even the tip of the iceberg."},{"time":222102,"text":"If you get a little baby, and you abuse it verbally,"},{"time":225704,"text":"its little brain sends out chemicals that are so destructive"},{"time":229161,"text":"that the little part of its brain that can tell good from bad just doesn't grow,"},{"time":233153,"text":"so you might have yourself a homegrown psychotic."},{"time":236608,"text":"If a soldier sees his friend blown up, his brain goes into"},{"time":240085,"text":"such high alarm that he can't actually put the experience into words,"},{"time":243599,"text":"so he just feels the horror over and over again."}]},{"cues":[{"time":246373,"text":"So here's my question. My question is, how come"},{"time":248746,"text":"when people have mental damage, it's always an active imagination?"},{"time":252791,"text":"How come every other organ in your body can get sick"},{"time":256010,"text":"and you get sympathy, except the brain?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":258714,"text":"I'd like to talk a little bit more about the brain,"},{"time":261113,"text":"because I know you like that here at TED,"},{"time":263144,"text":"so if you just give me a minute here, okay."},{"time":266597,"text":"Okay, let me just say, there's some good news."},{"time":268603,"text":"There is some good news. First of all, let me say,"},{"time":271885,"text":"we've come a long, long way."},{"time":274212,"text":"We started off as a teeny, teeny little one-celled amoeba,"},{"time":278253,"text":"tiny, just sticking onto a rock, and now, voila, the brain."},{"time":282850,"text":"Here we go. (Laughter)"},{"time":284750,"text":"This little baby has a lot of horsepower."},{"time":287115,"text":"It comes completely conscious. It's got state-of-the-art lobes."},{"time":291538,"text":"We've got the occipital lobe so we can actually see the world."},{"time":295131,"text":"We got the temporal lobe so we can actually hear the world."},{"time":297777,"text":"Here we've got a little bit of long-term memory,"},{"time":299396,"text":"so, you know that night you want to forget, when you got really drunk? Bye-bye! Gone. (Laughter)"},{"time":304633,"text":"So actually, it's filled with 100 billion neurons"},{"time":307953,"text":"just zizzing away, electrically transmitting information,"},{"time":311256,"text":"zizzing, zizzing. I'm going to give you a little side view here."},{"time":313976,"text":"I don't know if you can get that here. (Laughter)"},{"time":317568,"text":"So, zizzing away, and so — (Laughter) —"},{"time":321568,"text":"And for every one — I know, I drew this myself. Thank you."},{"time":325257,"text":"For every one single neuron, you can actually have"},{"time":328929,"text":"from 10,000 to 100,000 different connections"},{"time":332655,"text":"or dendrites or whatever you want to call it, and every time"},{"time":335917,"text":"you learn something, or you have an experience,"},{"time":338437,"text":"that bush grows, you know, that bush of information."},{"time":340710,"text":"Can you imagine, every human being is carrying"},{"time":343664,"text":"that equipment, even Paris Hilton? (Laughter)"},{"time":348587,"text":"Go figure."}]},{"cues":[{"time":350281,"text":"But I got a little bad news for you folks. I got some bad news."},{"time":353765,"text":"This isn't for the one in four. This is for the four in four."},{"time":356885,"text":"We are not equipped for the 21st century."},{"time":361065,"text":"Evolution did not prepare us for this. We just don't have the bandwidth,"},{"time":364814,"text":"and for people who say, oh, they're having a nice day,"},{"time":367397,"text":"they're perfectly fine, they're more insane than the rest of us."},{"time":370957,"text":"Because I'll show you where there might be a few glitches"},{"time":373481,"text":"in evolution. Okay, let me just explain this to you."},{"time":375925,"text":"When we were ancient man — (Laughter) —"},{"time":379486,"text":"millions of years ago, and we suddenly felt threatened"},{"time":383247,"text":"by a predator, okay? — (Laughter) —"},{"time":386949,"text":"we would — Thank you. I drew these myself. (Laughter)"},{"time":389897,"text":"Thank you very much. Thank you. Thank you. (Applause)"},{"time":393720,"text":"Thank you. Anyway, we would fill up with our own adrenaline"},{"time":397794,"text":"and our own cortisol, and then we'd kill or be killed,"},{"time":400412,"text":"we'd eat or we'd be eaten, and then suddenly we'd de-fuel,"},{"time":403682,"text":"and we'd go back to normal. Okay."},{"time":405615,"text":"So the problem is, nowadays, with modern man— (Laughter) —"},{"time":410897,"text":"when we feel in danger, we still fill up with our own chemical"},{"time":414664,"text":"but because we can't kill traffic wardens — (Laughter) —"},{"time":419299,"text":"or eat estate agents, the fuel just stays in our body"},{"time":424096,"text":"over and over, so we're in a constant state of alarm,"},{"time":426584,"text":"a constant state. And here's another thing that happened."},{"time":428317,"text":"About 150,000 years ago, when language came online,"},{"time":431422,"text":"we started to put words to this constant emergency,"},{"time":433847,"text":"so it wasn't just, \"Oh my God, there's a saber-toothed tiger,\""},{"time":436503,"text":"which could be, it was suddenly, \"Oh my God, I didn't send the email. Oh my God, my thighs are too fat."},{"time":440544,"text":"Oh my God, everybody can see I'm stupid. I didn't get invited to the Christmas party!\""},{"time":444549,"text":"So you've got this nagging loop tape that goes"},{"time":447035,"text":"over and over again that drives you insane, so,"},{"time":449571,"text":"you see what the problem is? What once made you safe"},{"time":452548,"text":"now drives you insane."},{"time":454354,"text":"I'm sorry to be the bearer of bad news, but somebody has to be."},{"time":457508,"text":"Your pets are happier than you are. (Laughter)"},{"time":463372,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":466268,"text":"So kitty cat, meow, happy happy happy, human beings, screwed. (Laughter)"},{"time":471423,"text":"Completely and utterly -- so, screwed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":473698,"text":"But my point is, if we don't talk about this stuff,"},{"time":476157,"text":"and we don't learn how to deal with our lives, it's not going"},{"time":478495,"text":"to be one in four. It's going to be four in four"},{"time":480969,"text":"who are really, really going to get ill in the upstairs department."},{"time":484232,"text":"And while we're at it, can we please stop the stigma?"},{"time":486759,"text":"Thank you. (Applause)"},{"time":493436,"text":"(Applause) Thank you."}]}]}